The paper deals with graph algorithms and data structures, specifically additive spanners and distance oracles. These topics are commonly studied in the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
